<%# Self-hosted brand fonts. Replaces the Google Fonts <link> dance:
    saves ~1.6s on first paint (no DNS to googleapis/gstatic, no CSS roundtrip),
    eliminates the privacy-leak of Google seeing every visitor's IP, and lets
    us cache for a year via Rails' default static asset headers.

    Both are variable fonts: one woff2 file serves all weights we use.
    Space Grotesk: 500/700/900 (hero, headings, labels)
    JetBrains Mono: 400/700 (body, code) %>

<%# Preload the hero font: H1 LCP element on every page uses it at 900. %>
<link rel="preload" as="font" type="font/woff2" crossorigin href="/fonts/space-grotesk.woff2">

<style>
  @font-face {
    font-family: "Space Grotesk";
    font-style: normal;
    font-weight: 500 900;
    font-display: swap;
    src: url("/fonts/space-grotesk.woff2") format("woff2-variations"),
         url("/fonts/space-grotesk.woff2") format("woff2");
  }
  @font-face {
    font-family: "JetBrains Mono";
    font-style: normal;
    font-weight: 400 700;
    font-display: swap;
    src: url("/fonts/jetbrains-mono.woff2") format("woff2-variations"),
         url("/fonts/jetbrains-mono.woff2") format("woff2");
  }
</style>
